definition: the end of fixed period in office/expiration of a term
to arrive at (place or time)/period/to become due/classifier for events, meetings, elections, sporting fixtures, years (of graduation)

sentences.english: Article 169. An independent director may submit his resignation before the expiration of his term.
sentences.chinese: 第一百六十九條獨立董事在任期屆滿錢可以提出辭職。

sentences.english: Mr Tung's five-year term ends in June 2000.
sentences.chinese: 董建華的五年任期將於二千年六月屆滿。

sentences.english: Prior to the expiration of a director's term, the shareholders' general committee may not remove him without cause.
sentences.chinese: 董事在任期屆滿前，股東大會不得無故解除其職務。

sentences.english: Prior to expiration of a director's term, the shareholders' committee may not remove him without cause.
sentences.chinese: 董事在任期屆滿前，股東會不得無故解除其職務。

sentences.english: A contract subject to a time of expiration is extinguished at such time.
sentences.chinese: 附終止期限的合同，自期限屆滿時失效。

sentences.english: The Andes Favored Trade Act expired last December.
sentences.chinese: 安地斯貿易優惠法已於去年十二月屆滿。

sentences.english: This provision shall also apply after lapse of the centralized custody period.
sentences.chinese: 繼續予以集中保管，集中保管期間屆滿後亦同。

sentences.english: However, the ESE can be large for resources with intermediate expiration granularity.
sentences.chinese: 然而，東南偏東可大量的資源與中間屆滿粒度。

sentences.english: The ownership of the leased asset is transferred to the lessee when the term of lease expires;
sentences.chinese: 在租賃期屆滿時，租賃資產的所有權轉移給承租人。

sentences.english: Which being expired, the same day all the army of the Lord went forth out of the land of Egypt.
sentences.chinese: 四百三十年屆滿的那一天，上主的軍旅離開了埃及。

sentences.english: This Contract shall terminate upon expiration of the Joint Venture Term.
sentences.chinese: 本合同在合營期限屆滿時終止。

sentences.english: Upon expiration, re-inspection and license renewal shall be conducted.
sentences.chinese: 有效期屆滿應當重新審查發證。

sentences.english: The President can be elected again at the expiration of his4 years in office.
sentences.chinese: 總統在四年任期屆滿時可以連選連任。

sentences.english: Nothing in this licence confers any right to a renewal thereof on its expiry or to the grant of a new licence.
sentences.chinese: 本牌照並無授予牌照屆滿時續期或批給新牌照的權利。

sentences.english: Those not reorganized shall be terminated in one year's time starting from the date of the implementation of this law.
sentences.chinese: 未重新組建的，自本法施行之日起屆滿一年時終止。

sentences.english: Mr. Trichet, 68, will retire at the end of October after an eight-year term.
sentences.chinese: 今年68歲，會在8年任期屆滿後在10月底退休。

definition: to expire/to run out/to come to an end
to ask sb to resign from a post
to set/to designate/to stipulate/to provide/to draw up/to formulate (rules etc)/stipulation
to continue in (a political) office/to serve for another term of office
